-- China’s Sinohydro May Rebuild Railroads in Serbia, Tanjug Says
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-11-30T15:16:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-30/china-s-sinohydro-may-rebuild-railroads-in-serbia-tanjug-says.html
China ’s Sinohydro Corp. is in talks
with  Serbia  about participating in rebuilding hundreds of
kilometers of rail track in the Balkan country,  Tanjug  reported,
citing Infrastructure Minister Milutin Mrkonjic.  Sinohydro may start the work as early as March on sections
of the main, north-south route, if it reaches an agreement with
the Serbian government, the report said, citing the minister.
Sinohydro decided to set up its main European office in
Belgrade, said the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
